I"Ú<p>Recently some colleagues and I have been trying to understand the roles of contributors in open source scientific software projects. We studied 7 well-known scientific software projects that were hosted on GitHub (including <a href="https://github.com/Chaste/Chaste">Chaste</a>, <a href="https://github.com/dib-lab/khmer/">Khmer</a>, and <a href="https://github.com/genn-team/genn">Genn</a>). For each selected project, we identified the roles played by different contributors by analyzing each projectsâ€™ documentation, websites, and other readily available sources. Using a mix of quantitative and qualitative data, we curate some findings that we believe are interesting for the broad Medium population. Here they are.</p>
